	(text "POWER"
		(at 10 190 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "fff9a447-5daf-4189-b9df-2169739fb65a")
	)
	(text "+3V3 is the single regulated logic rail: the ESP32 dev board, mux logic, encoder VCC,\nphototransistor pull-ups, and IR LED driver current all come from here (not raw VM_BATT)."
		(at 200 100 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.2 2.2)))
		(uuid "d05568a6-388e-474a-9f30-b96a1e4fae2a")
	)
	(text "VBAT_CELL1_SENSE = cell1 voltage (0-4.2V) scaled to <=2.9V.\nVBAT_PACK_SENSE = full pack voltage (0-8.4V) scaled to <=3.3V.\nFirmware computes cell2 = pack - cell1. Both wired to ESP32 ADC pins A2/A1\n(VBAT_PACK_SENSE/VBAT_CELL1_SENSE) -- see GPIO allocation table in PROJECT_NOTES.md."
		(at 20 20 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.2 2.2)))
		(uuid "87d729ca-f01f-4d09-9a7a-d70836bf451b")
	)
	(text "MOTOR DRIVER (socketed TB6612 breakout) + ENCODERS  --  2x N20-with-encoder motors"
		(at 10 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "4b2531e1-9b48-43a7-b3a4-ea784ebdd6ed")
	)
	(text "Breakout logic inputs: STBY, AIN1/AIN2, BIN1/BIN2 are plain ESP32 GPIO; PWMA/PWMB are\nESP32 LEDC PWM outputs (firmware configures PWM). VM=raw battery, VCC=+3V3 logic, GND common.\nAO1/AO2 -> motor A (MOTA_P/N), BO1/BO2 -> motor B (MOTB_P/N). The breakout's own board\ncarries VM/VCC decoupling. VERIFY the breakout's real pin order + row spacing before fab."
		(at 10 258 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "38ca532b-c80b-41f2-898e-f30b5f728c90")
	)
	(text "10k pull-ups on all 4 encoder lines -- defensive: N20-encoder wire-color-to-\nfunction mapping is unverified for the exact unit ordered (see PROJECT_NOTES.md),\nand encoder output stage (open-drain vs push-pull) isn't confirmed either. A pull-up\nis required if open-drain and harmless if push-pull.\nMotor connector pin order is FUNCTIONAL (M+,M-,ENC_VCC,ENC_GND,ENC_A,ENC_B) --\nverify against the real wire-to-pin mapping at assembly time, not assumed here."
		(at 10 400 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "56de4055-562b-46e1-ac37-aac0ec1e19fa")
	)
	(text "CONTROLLER  --  socketed Arduino Nano ESP32 (ESP32-S3): control + sensors + telemetry"
		(at 300 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "f78490b3-706c-4a57-babe-ded7111523a7")
	)
	(text "Single ESP32-S3 runs everything: TB6612 (STBY/PWMA/PWMB/AIN*/BIN*), 4 encoder inputs,\nthe 2x HEF4067 sensor muxes (MUX_S0-S3 select, MUX_SENSE ADC, LED_PULSE), the two\nbattery-sense ADCs, and USER_BTN. Wi-Fi/BLE telemetry is built in; flashed over the\nboard's own USB-C -- no separate programmer or UART relay. The 3 analog nets are on\nA0-A2 (real ADC pins). The Nano-ESP32 header-to-GPIO map, and which pins are\nstrapping/input-only, must be confirmed against the Arduino Nano ESP32 pinout in\nfirmware -- see PROJECT_NOTES.md."
		(at 300 360 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "e9c7c3a6-dfc6-48b0-83e3-e3df2e08dba4")
	)
	(text "CONNECTORS / DEBUG"
		(at 600 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "c7cbe155-8ad6-4a52-bbf6-b61413b4b832")
	)
	(text "USER_BTN (ESP32 A7) -- active-low start-run button, pulled up to +3V3.\nStandard micromouse UX (arm, then start a run). One of the ESP32 analog-capable\npins; the full net/pin allocation is in PROJECT_NOTES.md.\n\nNo separate debug/programming header on this board: the Arduino Nano ESP32 is\nflashed over its own onboard USB-C, and firmware is updated the same way (or\nover-the-air via Wi-Fi). No BOOT0/SWD/UART-relay hardware is needed now that the\nSTM32 is gone -- the ESP32's native USB handles programming and console."
		(at 600 260 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "aa9a286e-d7db-4aca-9f27-ebf81d76602e")
	)
	(text "IR SENSOR ARRAY  --  6 wall + 8 line sensors"
		(at 10 420 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "bcc5b2dd-7b7d-4130-81c8-f0c207930f59")
	)
	(text "2x HEF4067BT 16-ch analog mux/demux, sharing select lines MUX_S0-S3.\nEach sensor: SFH309 phototransistor (collector -> 47k pull-up to +3V3 AND to its\nread-mux channel; emitter -> GND) + SFH4550 IR LED (anode -> current-limit resistor\n-> +3V3; cathode -> BSS138 low-side switch drain; switch source -> GND; switch gate\n-> its write-demux channel). Firmware pulses LED_PULSE while stepping MUX_S0-S3\nthrough one channel at a time (crosstalk avoidance), sampling MUX_SENSE 'bright' then\n'ambient' with the LED off, subtracting -- see PROJECT_NOTES.md IR sensor circuit design.\nCurrent-limit resistor: 33ohm, sized for ~3.3V rail, SFH4550 Vf~1.35V typ, allowing\n~0.3-0.5V for the BSS138 switch's on-resistance at 3.3V gate drive (not independently\nverified against the BSS138 datasheet's Vgs=3.3V Rds(on) curve in this session --\ntune at bring-up if dimmer/brighter than expected)."
		(at 150 460 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "f623a6bc-14ba-47e4-815d-de1b6638c557")
	)
